src_text: Cabinet welcomed the successful State Visit to Kenya by President Cyril Ramaphosa, at the invitation of his Kenyan counterpart, Dr William Rut The visit included a Business Forum focusing on trade and investment between Kenya and South Afric The visit also resulted in the signing of instruments on cooperation in correctional services, human settlements, audio-visual co-production, and on building the capacity of the State with the National School of Governmen The two leaders discussed multilateral, economic, regional and continental issue
trg_text: Cabinet welcomed the successful State Visit to Kenya by President Cyril Ramaphosa, at the invitation of his Kenyan counterpart, Dr William Rut The visit included a Business Forum focusing on trade and investment between Kenya and South Afric The visit also resulted in the signing of instruments on cooperation in correctional services, human settlements, audio-visual co-production, and on building the capacity of the State with the National School of Governmen The two leaders discussed multilateral, economic, regional and continental issue

src_text: Kenya is South Africa s largest trading partner outside the Southern African Development Community (SADC) region, making South Africa the biggest seller of goods to Kenya on the continen South Africa exported over R6-billion worth of goods to Kenya in 2021.
trg_text: Kenya is South Africa s largest trading partner outside the Southern African Development Community (SADC) region, making South Africa the biggest seller of goods to Kenya on the continen South Africa exported over R6-billion worth of goods to Kenya in 2021.
